members.title: Characteristic Rock Types
members.text: A rock type r is characteristic for some time interval dt iff (i) r only exisits during dt and (ii) during dt, every region supports r #dat-met

members.title: Existence of Characteristic Rock Types
members.text: For every time intervall dt, there is some charactersitic rock type r #dat-met

members.title: CRTP - 2
members.text: If two strata support the same characteristic rock types, then they are of the same age #dat-met

members.title: Characteristic Rock Type Principle
members.text: There is a bijection between the age of some strata t and its characteristic rock types #dat-met

members.title: Characteristic Fossils
members.text: A fossil species f is characteristic for some time interval dt iff (i) f only exisits during dt and (ii) during dt, every region supports f #dat-met

members.title: Existence of Characteristic Fossils
members.text: For every time intervall dt, there is some charactersitic fossil species f #dat-met

members.title: CFP - 2
members.text: If two strata support the same characteristic fossils, then they are of the same age #dat-met

members.title: Characteristic Fossils Principle
members.text: There is a bijection between the age of some strata t and its characteristic fossils #dat-met

members.title: Lyellian Principle
members.text: At the earth's surface, there is a constant but piecemeal change in the composition of the faunas and floras, in correlation with ever-changing physical environments #dat-met

members.title: L2 - Maximal Difference in Fossils
members.text: If two strata are suffienciently different in age, then they do not support similar fossil species #dat-met
